#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:2
msgid "Configuration file reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:4
msgid ""
"Read the Docs supports configuring your documentation builds with a "
"configuration file. This file is named ``.readthedocs.yaml`` and should be "
"placed in the top level of your Git repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:7
msgid ""
"The ``.readthedocs.yaml``  file can contain a number of settings that are "
"not accessible through the Read the Docs website."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:11
msgid ""
"When using a monorepo, it is possible to place the ``.readthedocs.yaml`` "
"file in a subdirectory and configure a custom path from the project settings "
"dashboard. See the :doc:`/guides/setup/monorepo` documentation for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:16
msgid ""
"Because the file is stored in Git, the configuration will apply to the exact "
"version that is being built. **This allows you to store different "
"configurations for different versions of your documentation.**"
msgstr ""

