#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:498
msgid "build.apt_packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:500
msgid ""
"List of `APT packages`_ to install. Our build servers run various Ubuntu LTS "
"versions with the default set of package repositories installed. We don't "
"currently support PPA's or other custom repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:509
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"build:\n"
"  apt_packages:\n"
"    - libclang\n"
"    - cmake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:520
msgid ""
"When possible avoid installing Python packages using apt (``python3-numpy`` "
"for example), :doc:`use pip or conda instead </guides/reproducible-builds>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:525
msgid ""
"Currently, it's not possible to use this option when using :ref:`config-file/"
"v2:build.commands`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:529
msgid "build.jobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:531
msgid ""
"Commands to be run before or after a Read the Docs :term:`pre-defined build "
"jobs`, or to override a specific job. This allows you to run custom commands "
"at a particular moment in the build process. See :doc:`/build-customization` "
"for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:536
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: ubuntu-24.04\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.13\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    pre_create_environment:\n"
"      - echo \"Command run at 'pre_create_environment' step\"\n"
"    post_build:\n"
"      - echo \"Command run at 'post_build' step\"\n"
"      - echo `date`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:553
msgid ""
"Each build step consists of a list of commands to be executed. ``build.os`` "
"and ``build.tools`` are also required to use ``build.jobs``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:558
msgid ""
"If the :ref:`config-file/v2:sphinx` or  :ref:`config-file/v2:mkdocs` keys "
"are present in the configuration file, the default steps for each tool will "
"be executed for the ``create_environment``, ``install``, and ``build`` "
"steps. You can override any of these steps, but be aware that some steps may "
"depend on others, for example, the default ``install`` and ``build`` steps "
"depend on the ``create_environment`` step creating the Python virtual "
"environment in a specific directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:563
msgid ""
"If neither of the ``sphinx`` or ``mkdocs`` keys are present in the "
"configuration file, only the specified ``build.tools`` and ``build."
"apt_packages`` will be installed, you will in charge of generating the "
"documentation in the :ref:`$READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT <build-customization:where to "
"put files>` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:0
msgid "Allowed keys"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:568
msgid ""
"``post_checkout``, ``pre_system_dependencies``, "
"``post_system_dependencies``, ``pre_create_environment``, "
"``create_environment``, ``post_create_environment``, ``pre_install``, "
"``post_install``, ``pre_build``, ``build``, ``post_build``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:572 ../../../config-file/v2.rst:611
#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:869
msgid "``{}``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:575
msgid "build.jobs.build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:577
msgid ""
"Commands to override the default build process. When running builds from "
"pull requests, only the ``html`` step will be executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:580
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"formats: [pdf, epub]\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: ubuntu-24.04\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.13\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    create_environment:\n"
"      - echo \"Preparing environment\"\n"
"    install:\n"
"      - echo \"Installing dependencies\"\n"
"    build:\n"
"      html:\n"
"        - echo \"Building HTML\"\n"
"        - mkdir -p $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/html/\n"
"        - echo \"Hello world!\" > $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/html/index.html\n"
"      pdf:\n"
"        - echo \"Building PDF\"\n"
"        - mkdir -p $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/pdf/\n"
"        - echo \"Hello world!\" > $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/pdf/index.pdf\n"
"      epub:\n"
"        - echo \"Building ePub\"\n"
"        - mkdir -p $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/epub/\n"
"        - echo \"Hello world!\" > $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/epub/index.epub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:609
msgid "``html``, ``pdf``, ``epub``, ``htmlzip``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:615
msgid ""
"If any of the ``pdf``, ``epub``, or ``htmlzip`` steps are overridden, they "
"should be included in the :ref:`config-file/v2:formats` list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:620
msgid ""
"For each format, you need to generate their output in the :ref:"
"`$READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT <build-customization:where to put files>` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:623
msgid "build.commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:625
msgid ""
"Specify a list of commands that Read the Docs will run on the build process. "
"When ``build.commands`` is used, none of the :term:`pre-defined build jobs` "
"will be executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:628
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: ubuntu-24.04\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.13\"\n"
"  commands:\n"
"    - pip install pelican\n"
"    - pelican --settings docs/pelicanconf.py --output $READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/"
"html/ docs/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:640
msgid "But we recommend using :ref:`config-file/v2:build.jobs` instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:642
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"build:\n"
"  os: \"ubuntu-22.04\"\n"
"  tools:\n"
"    python: \"3.10\"\n"
"  jobs:\n"
"    install:\n"
"      - pip install pelican\n"
"    build:\n"
"      html:\n"
"        - pelican --settings docs/pelicanconf.py --output "
"$READTHEDOCS_OUTPUT/html/ docs/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:657
msgid ""
"``build.jobs`` offers the same functionality as ``build.commands``, but in a "
"more structured way that allows you to define different commands for each "
"format, while also supporting installing system dependencies via ``build."
"apt_packages``. See :doc:`/build-customization` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:664
msgid ""
"``build.os`` and ``build.tools`` are also required when using ``build."
"commands``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:668
msgid ""
"All items in the ``build.commands`` array are executed in a clean shell "
"environment, i.e. environment changes do not persist and the working "
"directory always start from the git repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:677
msgid "sphinx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:679
msgid "Configuration for Sphinx documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:681
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"sphinx:\n"
"  builder: html\n"
"  configuration: conf.py\n"
"  fail_on_warning: true"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:691
msgid ""
"If you want to pin Sphinx to a specific version, use a ``requirements.txt`` "
"or ``environment.yml`` file (see :ref:`config-file/v2:requirements file` "
"and  :ref:`config-file/v2:conda.environment`). If you are using a metadata "
"file to describe code dependencies like ``setup.py``, ``pyproject.toml``, or "
"similar, you can use the ``extra_requirements`` option (see :ref:`config-"
"file/v2:packages`). This also allows you to override :ref:`the default "
"pinning done by Read the Docs if your project was created before October "
"2020 <build-default-versions:external dependencies>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:702
msgid "sphinx.builder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:704
msgid "The builder type for the Sphinx documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:707
msgid "``html``, ``dirhtml``, ``singlehtml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:708
msgid "``html``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:711
msgid ""
"The ``htmldir`` builder option was renamed to ``dirhtml`` to use the same "
"name as sphinx. Configurations using the old name will continue working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:715
msgid "sphinx.configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:717
msgid "The path to the ``conf.py`` file, relative to the root of the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:723
msgid "sphinx.fail_on_warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:725
msgid ""
"Turn warnings into errors (:option:`-W <sphinx:sphinx-build.-W>` and :option:"
"`--keep-going <sphinx:sphinx-build.--keep-going>` options). This means the "
"build fails if there is a warning and exits with exit status 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:729 ../../../config-file/v2.rst:770
#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:840
msgid "``bool``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:733
msgid "mkdocs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:735
msgid "Configuration for MkDocs documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:737
msgid ""
"version: 2\n"
"\n"
"mkdocs:\n"
"  configuration: mkdocs.yml\n"
"  fail_on_warning: false"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:746
msgid ""
"If you want to pin MkDocs to a specific version, use a ``requirements.txt`` "
"or ``environment.yml`` file (see :ref:`config-file/v2:requirements file` "
"and  :ref:`config-file/v2:conda.environment`). If you are using a metadata "
"file to describe code dependencies like ``setup.py``, ``pyproject.toml``, or "
"similar, you can use the ``extra_requirements`` option (see :ref:`config-"
"file/v2:packages`). This also allows you to override :ref:`the default "
"pinning done by Read the Docs if your project was created before March 2021 "
"<build-default-versions:external dependencies>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:757
msgid "mkdocs.configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:759
msgid ""
"The path to the ``mkdocs.yml`` file, relative to the root of the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:765
msgid "mkdocs.fail_on_warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../config-file/v2.rst:767
msgid ""
"`Turn warnings into errors <https://www.mkdocs.org/user-guide/configuration/"
"#strict>`__. This means that the build stops at the first warning and exits "
"with exit status 1."
